{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5b39e6d8-f7fa-4c39-b2a6-065940ff44e0","content":"Here are the programmatic approaches, from simplest to most granular:\n\n## 1. Use the built-in MSBuild target (recommended for CI)\n\n```bash\n# Create a temp project, then let the SDK tell you what it needs AND install it:\ndotnet new maui -n Tmp && cd Tmp\ndotnet build -t:InstallAndroidDependencies \\\n  -f net9.0-android \\\n  -p:AndroidSdkDirectory=$ANDROID_HOME \\\n  -p:AcceptAndroidSDKLicenses=true\n```\n\nThis installs *exactly* the packages your SDK version requires — no guessing.\n\n## 2. Query MSBuild properties (to read without installing)\n\n```bash\ndotnet new maui -n Tmp && cd Tmp\ndotnet msbuild -getProperty:AndroidSdkBuildToolsVersion \\\n               -getProperty:AndroidDefaultTargetDotnetApiLevel \\\n               -f net9.0-android\n```\n\nKey properties:\n| Property | Meaning |\n|----------|---------|\n| `AndroidSdkBuildToolsVersion` | e.g. `34.0.0` |\n| `AndroidDefaultTargetDotnetApiLevel` | target API level |\n| `AndroidSdkCommandLineToolsVersion` | cmdline-tools version |\n\n## 3. Inspect the workload pack directly\n\n```bash\nSDK_PATH=$(dotnet --list-sdks | awk '{print $2}' | tr -d '[]')\nPACK_DIR=\"$SDK_PATH/../packs/Microsoft.Android.Sdk.Linux\"\n# Find the targets file that defines the versions:\ngrep -r \"AndroidSdkBuildToolsVersion\\|CommandLineTools\" \\\n  \"$PACK_DIR\"/*/tools/Xamarin.Android.Sdk.DefaultProperties.targets\n```\n\nThat `.targets` file is the authoritative source — it ships inside the workload pack and defines every version literal.\n\n---\n\n**For CI**, approach #1 is the gold standard: it's idempotent, uses `sdkmanager` internally, and always matches your exact SDK. You can run it in a setup step before your actual build.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d9105498-549d-4f70-ad96-5e535e6068da","outputTokens":515,"requestId":"5012:D447C:1C858DC:1F8EBF7:69FA90E2"},"id":"a9dabde5-47ec-46e4-a20f-2e4a36966138","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:53:02.069Z","parentId":"c9a4b37a-809c-4a19-b9d5-5076039d6d5e"}
